          <name>HIPDNN_HEUR_MODE_FALLBACK</name>
          <initializer>= 0</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Fallback mode - functional support only. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Returns engines that are functionally correct for the given operation graph. No performance tuning or optimization is performed. This is the most reliable mode for finding a working configuration.</para>
<para>Use this mode when:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>You need guaranteed functional correctness</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Performance is not critical</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>You want the fastest engine discovery </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Heuristic modes for engine discovery. </para>
        </briefdescription>
